location: 3264 Irma ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8Z3R8, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson

Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite . There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST,  BC, V8W 1L6, CA

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: 108 Niagara ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8V1E9, CA

Get ready for a night of Latin rhythm and Irish luck! Join us for St. Patrick’s Latin Night featuring Salsa, Bachata, and Merengue with a festive green & gold celebration. Enjoy an intro class at 8:00 PM followed by a social dance from 8:30 PM. Dress in green, gold, or white for added fun!
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St., Victoria, BC,  BC, V8Z 3K9, CA

description: Intermediate Sensual Bachata Workshop on March 20. The 2-hour workshop (8:00–9:30 PM with a practice session 9:30–10:00 PM) focuses on advanced variations of the Madrid pass, smooth transitions, and musicality. No partner needed; just bring your energy and comfortable shoes. Registration at maximumotion@gmail.com.
location: Method Studio, 841 Fisgard St, Victoria, British Columbia,  BC, V8W 1R9, CA

description: Celebrate the vibrant spirit of Carnaval with an evening of Latin social dancing at 111 Superior St. The event features doors opening at 4:15 PM, a beginner dance lesson from 4:30-5:00 PM, and social dancing from 5:00-8:30 PM. This is part of a recurring monthly series held on the last Sunday of every month from September to May.
location: 111 Superior ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8V1T2, CA
price: $15 for General Admission, $12 for Students

description: Imagine yourself transported into a Regency-era ball at the historic Crystal Ballroom of the Fairmont Empress Hotel. The event features dancing, live music, food, and optional dance lessons at The White Eagle Polish Hall with costume rental options available. A detailed agenda outlines dinner, multiple dance performances, and other festive activities.
location: Fairmont Empress, 721 Government Street, Victoria, British Columbia,  BC, V8W 1W5, CA

description: 30 min technique class for everyone before practica! Let’s start 2025 with a good exercise routine that will strengthen and stretch out tango bodies. Recurring dates include: Wed, 5 Mar; Wed, 12 Mar; Wed, 19 Mar (+8 more).
location: Alive Tango Victoria, 1303 Broad St., Victoria, British Columbia,  BC, V8W 2A8, CA

description: Sensual Bachata classes in March! Beginner’s workshop: Perfect for total beginners or for those looking to refine their basics! event_name: The Social - Latin Dance Night - Bachata Vibes
description: Welcome to The Social - Bachata Vibes Edition, a fun night of dancing to great Latin Music. This weekend we are bringing the Bachata Vibes with 50% bachata music, as well as a mix of salsa, merengue and cha-cha-cha. Includes an intro bachata lesson at 7pm and social dancing until 10:30pm. No partner, no experience required.

description: Recurring Thursday event at Ukrainian Cultural Centre.
